00:22:43,235 --> 00:22:44,236
- I'll--
- No.

267
00:22:44,779 --> 00:22:46,113
It's okay. I'll throw it out.

268
00:22:46,197 --> 00:22:47,365
Oh, sure.

269
00:23:16,727 --> 00:23:17,728
BAEK AH-JIN

270
00:23:17,812 --> 00:23:20,856
If you ever feel like helping me,
call me then.

271
00:23:21,607 --> 00:23:24,568
Otherwise, don't get in my way
for no reason.

272
00:23:58,102 --> 00:23:59,186
It's Baek Ah-jin!

273
00:25:07,963 --> 00:25:11,425
You're aware the award show is airing
on a different channel now, right?

274
00:25:12,426 --> 00:25:16,222
They say the Best Actress Award is
basically guaranteed to go to her.

275
00:25:17,014 --> 00:25:18,265
That actually works out better.

276
00:25:20,226 --> 00:25:22,144
Because her final appearance

277
00:25:23,354 --> 00:25:26,482
will stay in people's memories
as her most beautiful one.

278
00:25:29,860 --> 00:25:32,738
DIM HEART: TWO FACES OF AN ACTRESS

279
00:25:33,531 --> 00:25:36,242
NOTABLE TRAITS:
ANTISOCIAL PERSONALITY DISORDER

280
00:25:36,325 --> 00:25:38,619
FOUND IN ABOUT 4 PERCENT
OF THE POPULATION

281
00:25:42,873 --> 00:25:43,916
Baek Ah-jin.

282
00:25:47,962 --> 00:25:49,755
She falls within the four percent
of the population

283
00:25:49,838 --> 00:25:51,423
with antisocial personality disorder.

284
00:25:54,385 --> 00:25:55,886
She views others as tools

285
00:25:55,970 --> 00:25:58,556
and manipulates or uses them
to achieve her goals.

286
00:25:58,847 --> 00:26:02,393
At the biggest annual event
in Korean cinema

287
00:26:02,851 --> 00:26:08,774
Baek Ah-jin stands
as a top contender for Best Actress

288
00:26:09,108 --> 00:26:12,278
drawing intense attention
from media and fans alike.

289
00:26:19,743 --> 00:26:21,745
She has never
physically committed murder

290
00:26:21,829 --> 00:26:23,664
but she caused
the deaths of two people.

291
00:26:26,917 --> 00:26:30,170
She has deliberately approached
only men who were of use to her.

292
00:26:33,591 --> 00:26:36,468
She still harbors
an unfulfilled plan to kill.

293
00:26:42,975 --> 00:26:45,728
She is Baek Ah-jin, an actress.

294
00:27:24,058 --> 00:27:26,685
Now, let us begin

295
00:27:26,769 --> 00:27:28,854
the 46th Bluedragon Awards.

296
00:27:28,937 --> 00:27:30,689
Let's get started.

297
00:27:39,657 --> 00:27:40,741
Baek Ah-jin is

298
00:27:40,824 --> 00:27:42,743
the strongest candidate
for Best Actress, right?

299
00:27:42,826 --> 00:27:44,912
If she wins, ratings will explode.

300
00:27:45,162 --> 00:27:46,705
Don't tell her anything beforehand.

301
00:27:46,997 --> 00:27:49,041
Make sure no one gets near her.
Got it?

302
00:27:49,124 --> 00:27:50,626
...Song Kyeong-su.

303
00:27:51,794 --> 00:27:52,795
DIM HEART

304
00:27:53,295 --> 00:27:54,296
Baek Ah-jin.

305
00:27:56,173 --> 00:27:58,884
The elegant and kind actress.

306
00:28:00,219 --> 00:28:01,261
Baek Ah-jin?

307
00:28:01,845 --> 00:28:03,597
She was the epitome of perfection.

308
00:28:03,681 --> 00:28:05,307
She was smart, kind, and pretty.

309
00:28:05,933 --> 00:28:07,851
She stood out wherever she was.

310
00:28:08,936 --> 00:28:11,563
Everyone at our school knew her.

311
00:28:12,272 --> 00:28:14,775
Even the teachers adored her.

312
00:28:15,359 --> 00:28:19,905
But those who knew her well
tell a completely different story.

313
00:28:20,864 --> 00:28:22,032
We met those people.

314
00:28:23,784 --> 00:28:26,412
What do I think of Baek Ah-jin?

315
00:28:27,955 --> 00:28:30,082
A devil wearing human skin.

316
00:28:30,332 --> 00:28:31,417
She didn't have a mother.

317
00:28:32,418 --> 00:28:33,919
And her father was a criminal.

318
00:28:34,002 --> 00:28:36,630
She wasn't normal,
at least from what I felt.

319
00:28:37,798 --> 00:28:40,342
It always seemed like her emotions
were rehearsed, as if she was acting.

320
00:28:40,718 --> 00:28:43,053
Her acting has
always been exceptional.

321
00:28:43,137 --> 00:28:45,723
She switched masks
whenever it suited her needs.

322
00:28:45,806 --> 00:28:48,267
That's why I could never tell
what she was thinking.

323
00:28:48,350 --> 00:28:52,062
I think she has
very little empathy for others.

324
00:28:52,146 --> 00:28:54,356
I figured that was the case.

325
00:28:55,524 --> 00:28:57,985
I even recommended
she get psychological counseling.

326
00:28:58,068 --> 00:28:59,278
TRUE LOVE COUNSELING CENTER

327
00:28:59,361 --> 00:29:01,071
Check this out.
It's about Baek Ah-jin.

328
00:29:01,864 --> 00:29:03,240
Is this for real?

329
00:29:03,323 --> 00:29:04,825
Isn't she terrifying?

330
00:29:04,908 --> 00:29:06,535
How can a human being do this?

331
00:29:06,869 --> 00:29:10,247
Now, we'll move on to the highly
anticipated Best Actress Award.

332
00:29:10,622 --> 00:29:15,377
Last year's winner, Jin Seo-gyeong,
will be joining us to present it.

333
00:29:15,461 --> 00:29:17,004
Please give her a round of applause.

334
00:29:18,839 --> 00:29:20,674
Hello, I'm Jin Seo-gyeong.

335
00:29:22,176 --> 00:29:23,302
Let me announce the winner.

336
00:29:24,261 --> 00:29:25,721
The Best Actress Award

337
00:29:26,305 --> 00:29:28,724
at the 46th Bluedragon Awards...

338
00:29:30,768 --> 00:29:31,769
goes to...

339
00:29:37,566 --> 00:29:39,735
Baek Ah-jin for Amen to Nothing.

340
00:29:39,818 --> 00:29:41,111
Congratulations.

341
00:29:50,662 --> 00:29:52,623
Baek Ah-jin,
the winner of the Best Actress Award

342
00:29:52,706 --> 00:29:54,291
portrayed a nun in Amen to Nothing

343
00:29:54,374 --> 00:29:57,002
who investigates the tragedy
that befell her family

344
00:29:57,085 --> 00:29:59,379
and carries out revenge

345
00:29:59,463 --> 00:30:01,089
delivering a deeply moving

346
00:30:01,173 --> 00:30:03,300
and introspective performance
about a character

347
00:30:03,383 --> 00:30:05,177
in anguish over religious doubts.

348
00:30:05,677 --> 00:30:07,387
Congratulations
from the bottom of our hearts.

349
00:30:24,154 --> 00:30:25,322
Thank you.

350
00:30:27,825 --> 00:30:29,409
First of all

351
00:30:30,244 --> 00:30:31,495
my mom

352
00:30:33,121 --> 00:30:34,122
in heaven.

353
00:30:35,833 --> 00:30:36,917
How do I look, Mom?

354
00:30:40,379 --> 00:30:41,380
Are you proud of me?

355
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:43,423
Her mother died in an accident.

356
00:30:44,758 --> 00:30:47,553
Her father was
the victim of a murder case.

357
00:30:47,636 --> 00:30:50,889
She was also present
at her lover's grandmother's death

358
00:30:50,973 --> 00:30:53,392
and later, her lover took
his own life.

359
00:30:54,393 --> 00:30:56,436
For one person
to experience all of this

360
00:30:56,520 --> 00:30:58,981
the coincidences seem too extreme.

361
00:30:59,356 --> 00:31:00,899
- A documentary about Ah-jin is out.
- What?

362
00:31:00,983 --> 00:31:02,109
That's a scoop.

363
00:31:02,484 --> 00:31:03,819
Start preparing for revisions.

364
00:31:03,902 --> 00:31:06,446
- Check if any articles are out.
- Yes, sir.

365
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:11,618
While working on Amen to Nothing

366
00:31:12,536 --> 00:31:14,872
I couldn't help but wonder...

367
00:31:16,874 --> 00:31:19,042
"Where is my God?"

368
00:31:21,003 --> 00:31:22,504
Looking back

369
00:31:24,256 --> 00:31:25,257
I realized

370
00:31:26,758 --> 00:31:28,135
He was inside me all along.

371
00:31:30,220 --> 00:31:31,263
I grew up

372
00:31:32,347 --> 00:31:34,141
in an unfortunate environment.

373
00:31:35,851 --> 00:31:40,188
But luck always followed me.

374
00:31:40,439 --> 00:31:41,857
I thought we were incredibly lucky.

375
00:31:42,316 --> 00:31:44,109
I caught myself wondering
if she was an angel

376
00:31:44,192 --> 00:31:45,819
who had come down for my brother.

377
00:31:46,486 --> 00:31:49,156
But I overheard something
at my grandma's funeral.

378
00:31:49,781 --> 00:31:51,033
Was it someone in the film industry?

379
00:31:51,116 --> 00:31:53,076
Apparently, she was smiling
in front of him.

380
00:31:56,747 --> 00:32:02,002
Every step I took to get here

381
00:32:02,794 --> 00:32:04,379
wasn't easy.

382
00:32:05,839 --> 00:32:07,424
But I never stopped.

383
00:32:07,966 --> 00:32:09,509
I kept moving forward

384
00:32:11,178 --> 00:32:12,888
and eventually, I got here.

385
00:32:14,973 --> 00:32:17,684
Her acting has
always been exceptional.

386
00:32:17,768 --> 00:32:20,479
She switched masks
whenever it suited her needs.

387
00:32:22,314 --> 00:32:24,149
To everyone who walked with me

388
00:32:24,983 --> 00:32:27,361
on my journey to today

389
00:32:30,364 --> 00:32:31,949
I offer my sincere gratitude.

390
00:32:32,449 --> 00:32:34,409
She used the people around her

391
00:32:34,493 --> 00:32:36,912
to make me look
like an idiot and a thief.

392
00:32:37,287 --> 00:32:41,458
Could she have used our boss
to try to kill her own father?

393
00:32:41,541 --> 00:32:44,127
We were like family
when she was dating my brother.

394
00:32:44,670 --> 00:32:46,713
I thought she'd at least
show up once at the funeral.

395
00:32:49,174 --> 00:32:50,258
I was stunned.

396
00:32:50,884 --> 00:32:53,845
Soon after, news came out
that she was marrying a chaebol.

397
00:32:58,141 --> 00:32:59,518
I was like, "What?"

398
00:33:04,523 --> 00:33:07,317
These testimonies about Baek Ah-jin

399
00:33:07,401 --> 00:33:09,611
are not easy to verify.

400
00:33:10,862 --> 00:33:13,740
So, we wondered
whether continuing this investigation

401
00:33:13,824 --> 00:33:15,367
was the right thing to do.

402
00:33:15,742 --> 00:33:17,869
Then, we learned something new.

403
00:33:18,704 --> 00:33:19,955
Rumors surrounding

404
00:33:20,414 --> 00:33:24,209
the suspicious death of her father,
Baek Seon-gyu.

405
00:33:25,377 --> 00:33:29,715
Dim Heart began to track down
the truth of that day.

406
00:33:32,134 --> 00:33:35,679
There were three primary suspects
in this case.

407
00:33:37,222 --> 00:33:39,307
Former baseball player, Mr. Choi.

408
00:33:41,643 --> 00:33:43,770
And the person who was
consistently abused by the victim

409
00:33:43,854 --> 00:33:46,815
and thus had the clearest motive,
the victim's daughter

410
00:33:47,149 --> 00:33:48,233
actress Baek Ah-jin

411
00:33:48,316 --> 00:33:50,152
BAEK AH-JIN
ANTISOCIAL PERSONALITY DISORDER

412
00:33:50,235 --> 00:33:51,403
I remember that case.

413
00:33:51,486 --> 00:33:53,530
It was very unusual.

414
00:33:54,031 --> 00:33:57,492
There was only one victim
but multiple potential perpetrators.

415
00:33:57,576 --> 00:34:00,454
Among them, the one
with the clearest motive was

416
00:34:00,954 --> 00:34:02,497
the victim's daughter, Baek Ah-jin.

417
00:34:09,463 --> 00:34:10,505
Lastly

418
00:34:11,590 --> 00:34:13,550
to everyone

419
00:34:14,176 --> 00:34:15,969
who loved my performance

420
00:34:16,511 --> 00:34:19,306
and showed enthusiasm for my work

421
00:34:19,931 --> 00:34:22,059
and to those who supported me
not only as an actress

422
00:34:22,893 --> 00:34:24,102
but as a person.

423
00:34:24,811 --> 00:34:26,438
I give this glory to you.

424
00:34:31,068 --> 00:34:32,694
I sincerely thank you.

425
00:35:23,161 --> 00:35:26,456
The final suspect provided
our team with a decisive tip.

426
00:35:27,165 --> 00:35:29,626
It was Yoon Seok-ha,
the author of Co-Offender Y.

427
00:35:34,840 --> 00:35:36,383
The incident back then

428
00:35:37,509 --> 00:35:39,177
was planned from the beginning.

429
00:35:40,470 --> 00:35:42,848
It's true that Ah-jin
deliberately sought out

430
00:35:42,931 --> 00:35:44,683
someone kind enough to act for her.

431
00:35:45,350 --> 00:35:48,270
It's also true that
she found Choi Jung-ho and used him.

432
00:35:49,396 --> 00:35:52,357
It would have been easy for her
to win someone over

433
00:35:52,858 --> 00:35:54,234
and set a trap.

434
00:35:55,235 --> 00:35:56,486
Back then

435
00:35:57,195 --> 00:35:59,364
she even had a stalker decoy to use.

436
00:36:00,657 --> 00:36:04,369
When the said stalker hit her,
she immediately called Mr. Choi

437
00:36:04,452 --> 00:36:06,538
so he rushed over.

438
00:36:06,997 --> 00:36:08,832
But it wasn't a stalker.

439
00:36:13,962 --> 00:36:16,756
The person Choi struck
with the bat was...

440
00:36:16,840 --> 00:36:19,050
Seeing you alive
wasn't part of my plan.

441
00:36:19,134 --> 00:36:21,553
...the man disguised
to look like her stalker.

442
00:36:23,096 --> 00:36:24,472
It was her father

443
00:36:24,973 --> 00:36:26,433
Baek Seon-gyu.

444
00:36:40,363 --> 00:36:43,825
When I arrived, Choi was already gone

445
00:36:43,909 --> 00:36:46,161
and Baek Seon-gyu
was lying on the floor.

446
00:36:46,536 --> 00:36:47,829
There was blood everywhere

447
00:36:47,913 --> 00:36:49,956
so I assumed he was dead.

448
00:36:53,168 --> 00:36:54,711
Then, I saw Ah-jin.

449
00:36:59,758 --> 00:37:01,760
She was sitting
against the bathroom wall

450
00:37:01,843 --> 00:37:04,512
holding the bat.

451
00:37:16,775 --> 00:37:18,026
She looked at me and said

452
00:37:19,569 --> 00:37:20,654
"It's over."

453
00:37:25,742 --> 00:37:27,160
That's what she said.

454
00:37:28,536 --> 00:37:29,704
"It's all over."

455
00:37:57,190 --> 00:38:00,193
Other people's suffering
meant nothing to her.

456
00:38:01,278 --> 00:38:04,364
She only ever used people
to achieve her own goals

457
00:38:05,699 --> 00:38:06,700
and discarded them.

458
00:38:10,203 --> 00:38:11,371
That's how she built...

459
00:38:14,749 --> 00:38:16,209
her current position.

460
00:39:39,876 --> 00:39:41,252
Do you want to go somewhere?

461
00:39:43,755 --> 00:39:45,256
Anywhere

462
00:39:46,174 --> 00:39:47,258
without people.

463
00:40:13,701 --> 00:40:16,579
I thought you'd change
if I waited long enough.

464
00:40:18,623 --> 00:40:19,707
But you didn't.

465
00:40:21,126 --> 00:40:23,211
I realized that far too late.

466
00:40:24,129 --> 00:40:25,880
That I couldn't save you

467
00:40:26,798 --> 00:40:29,342
and that I was clinging
to something impossible.

468
00:40:31,719 --> 00:40:33,763
That you could never change.

469
00:40:34,973 --> 00:40:35,974
Exactly.

470
00:40:37,517 --> 00:40:39,894
And you realized
that simple thing too late.

471
00:40:41,062 --> 00:40:43,064
So what? Do you regret it now?

472
00:40:48,319 --> 00:40:49,320
No.

473
00:40:52,532 --> 00:40:55,243
Because now,
I'm the only one who can handle you.

474
00:40:59,581 --> 00:41:01,624
Handle me how?

475
00:41:03,710 --> 00:41:05,336
I have nowhere to go anymore.

476
00:41:07,172 --> 00:41:08,631
If you truly have nowhere to go

477
00:41:09,424 --> 00:41:11,426
how about we go to hell together

478
00:41:11,801 --> 00:41:12,802
Ah-jin?

479
00:41:18,141 --> 00:41:19,642
Are you being serious?

480
00:41:24,022 --> 00:41:26,274
I already decided
to stay with you to the end.

481
00:41:27,859 --> 00:41:29,652
If you stop now

482
00:41:29,986 --> 00:41:31,279
I'll stop, too.

483
00:41:33,656 --> 00:41:34,657
What will you do?

484
00:41:50,965 --> 00:41:54,260
I thought there was nothing left
that could tie me down.

485
00:42:02,310 --> 00:42:03,311
But it was you.

486
00:42:06,147 --> 00:42:07,440
My final shackle.

487
00:42:30,630 --> 00:42:32,507
Let's not do anything anymore.

488
00:42:39,847 --> 00:42:41,307
So that no one gets hurt

489
00:42:43,268 --> 00:42:44,769
we'll only look at each other.

490
00:42:53,778 --> 00:42:54,779
I love you...

491
00:42:58,116 --> 00:42:59,284
Ah-jin.

492
00:43:39,824 --> 00:43:43,745
Last night, the car driven
by author Yoon Seok-ha

493
00:43:43,828 --> 00:43:46,998
crashed into a guardrail
and fell off a cliff.

494
00:43:47,582 --> 00:43:51,044
The driver, Yoon Seok-ha,
died at the scene

495
00:43:51,502 --> 00:43:53,546
and actress Baek Ah-jin,
believed to be the passenger

496
00:43:53,630 --> 00:43:54,756
is currently missing.

497
00:43:55,465 --> 00:43:58,134
The police are investigating
the exact cause of the accident.

498
00:43:58,217 --> 00:44:00,053
WRITER YOON SEOK-HA DEAD,
ACTRESS BAEK AH-JIN MISSING

499
00:44:05,433 --> 00:44:06,768
At some point

500
00:44:07,935 --> 00:44:13,232
your presence started feeling
like a blade stuck in my heart.

501
00:44:16,569 --> 00:44:20,156
Even in death, I wouldn't be able
to understand or forgive you.

502
00:44:22,992 --> 00:44:26,704
So, in this life, I wanted to cleanly
sever anything tied to you and leave.

503
00:44:28,790 --> 00:44:31,626
And I wanted to disappear

504
00:44:32,543 --> 00:44:33,795
from your life, too.

505
00:44:35,088 --> 00:44:36,714
That's the best choice.

506
00:44:39,967 --> 00:44:43,221
I gave you
one last brief moment of happiness

507
00:44:44,722 --> 00:44:45,723
so you can live

508
00:44:46,683 --> 00:44:48,643
the rest of your life
with that in mind.

509
00:44:50,770 --> 00:44:53,690
Maybe this is
the first and last long revenge

510
00:44:56,192 --> 00:44:57,902
I'll ever give you, Mom.

511
00:44:59,320 --> 00:45:01,072
No, Jun-seo.

512
00:45:03,324 --> 00:45:04,450
Jun-seo.

513
00:45:04,534 --> 00:45:07,787
I hope you stay healthy.

514
00:45:07,870 --> 00:45:09,122
Jun-seo!

515
00:45:14,168 --> 00:45:15,169
Jun-seo!

516
00:45:56,878 --> 00:45:58,588
You can't find her anywhere?

517
00:46:01,382 --> 00:46:04,218
No signs of life or trace anywhere?

518
00:46:06,262 --> 00:46:07,513
Fine, never mind.

519
00:46:07,889 --> 00:46:09,098
You don't have to go that far.

520
00:46:09,182 --> 00:46:10,433
ACTRESS BAEK AH-JIN STILL MISSING

521
00:46:10,516 --> 00:46:12,018
Just leave the broadcast

522
00:46:12,101 --> 00:46:14,395
and respond
when they ask for cooperation.

523
00:46:16,689 --> 00:46:19,942
We want to share
a follow-up to our previous broadcast

524
00:46:20,026 --> 00:46:22,361
"Two Faces of an Actress."

525
00:46:22,904 --> 00:46:24,947
We recently learned that Yoon Jun-seo

526
00:46:25,031 --> 00:46:26,866
our informant
and the author of Co-Offender Y

527
00:46:27,325 --> 00:46:29,827
passed away not long ago.

